{"article_id":"H7p4W9b2cN6WmuCz","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Story highlights","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Doctor","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"who survived Ebola","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"says :","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"`` It is a fire straight from the pit of hell ''","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"Obama says","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"`` the world is looking to '' the U.S. for leadership on Ebola","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"Obama to call on Congress to approve $ 88 million more","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"After an in-person briefing from the staff at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention in Atlanta , President Barack Obama on Tuesday announced a `` major increase '' in the U.S. response to the Ebola outbreak in West Africa .","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"The United States will send troops , material","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"to build field hospitals , additional health care workers , community care kits and badly needed medical supplies .","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"Countless taxis","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"filled with families","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"worried","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"they 've become infected with Ebola","depth":11},{"id":15,"text":"currently crisscross Monrovia in search of help .","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"They scour the Liberian capital ,","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"but not one clinic can take them in for treatment .","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"`` Today , there is not one single bed available for the treatment of an Ebola patient in the entire country of Liberia , ''","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"said Margaret Chan , the World Health Organization 's director-general .","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"Obama :","depth":12},{"id":22,"text":"Ebola threat could become 'global '","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"MUST WATCH Obama :","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"Ebola threat could become 'global '","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"03:38","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"WHO :","depth":13},{"id":29,"text":"West Africa ca n't keep up with Ebola","depth":13},{"id":30,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"MUST WATCH WHO :","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"West Africa ca n't keep up with Ebola","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"01:34","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":14},{"id":35,"text":"'Not 1 bed ' available for Ebola patients","depth":14},{"id":36,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":13},{"id":37,"text":"MUST WATCH 'Not 1 bed ' available for Ebola patients 04:02","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"`` As soon as a new Ebola treatment facility is opened ,","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"it immediately fills to overflowing with patients , ''","depth":13},{"id":40,"text":"the WHO said .","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"Hospitals and clinics in Guinea , Liberia and Sierra Leone","depth":14},{"id":42,"text":"-- the countries","depth":15},{"id":43,"text":"hit hardest by the outbreak --","depth":15},{"id":44,"text":"are overwhelmed by what the WHO is calling the deadliest Ebola outbreak in history .","depth":13},{"id":45,"text":"The virus has killed at least 2,400 people ,","depth":14},{"id":46,"text":"and thousands more are infected .","depth":14},{"id":47,"text":"And there are now cases in Nigeria and Senegal .","depth":13},{"id":48,"text":"`` The number of new cases is increasing exponentially , ''","depth":14},{"id":49,"text":"the WHO said ,","depth":14},{"id":50,"text":"calling the situation a `` dire emergency with ... unprecedented dimensions of human suffering . ''","depth":13},{"id":51,"text":"`` Men and women and children are just sitting ,","depth":14},{"id":52,"text":"waiting to die right now , ''","depth":14},{"id":53,"text":"Obama said .","depth":13},{"id":54,"text":"`` This is a daunting task ,","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"but here 's what gives us hope .","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"The world knows how to fight this disease .","depth":15},{"id":57,"text":"It 's not a mystery .","depth":15},{"id":58,"text":"We know the science .","depth":15},{"id":59,"text":"We know how to prevent it from spreading .","depth":16},{"id":60,"text":"We know how to care for those","depth":18},{"id":61,"text":"who contract it .","depth":18},{"id":62,"text":"We know","depth":18},{"id":63,"text":"that","depth":19},{"id":64,"text":"if we take the proper steps ,","depth":20},{"id":65,"text":"we can save lives .","depth":20},{"id":66,"text":"But we have to act fast , ''","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"Obama said .","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"`` We ca n't dawdle on this one .","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"We have to move with force","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"and make sure","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"that we are catching this","depth":14},{"id":72,"text":"as best we can ,","depth":14},{"id":73,"text":"given that it has already broken out in ways","depth":14},{"id":74,"text":"that we have not seen before . ''","depth":14},{"id":75,"text":"The CDC already has hundreds of professionals on the ground in what the President described as the `` largest international response in the history of the CDC . ''","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"Maj. Gen. Darryl Williams , commander of the U.S. Army Africa , arrived in Liberia on Tuesday .","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"Liberian leadership asked","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"that the U.S. military step in","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"to help support civilian efforts there .","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"Williams will coordinate the military 's efforts","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"to improve logistics ,","depth":14},{"id":82,"text":"to build additional field hospitals","depth":15},{"id":83,"text":"and to create what the President called an `` air bridge ''","depth":16},{"id":84,"text":"to bring in additional supplies and health care workers .","depth":16},{"id":85,"text":"The effort will be called Operation United Assistance .","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"The new treatment centers may house up to 1,700 additional beds .","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"American military personnel in the region could increase by 3,000 ,","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"administration officials said .","depth":13},{"id":89,"text":"The U.S. will also create a new training facility","depth":13},{"id":90,"text":"to help prepare thousands more health care workers","depth":14},{"id":91,"text":"to handle sick patients .","depth":14},{"id":92,"text":"U.S. medics will train up to 500 health care workers per week","depth":13},{"id":93,"text":"to identify and care for people with Ebola .","depth":13},{"id":94,"text":"USAID will give 400,000 treatment kits with sanitizer and other protective items like gloves to families","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"to help them protect their own safety","depth":13},{"id":96,"text":"as they care for sick relatives .","depth":13},{"id":97,"text":"The President also called on Congress to approve additional funding","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"his administration requested","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"to carry on these critical efforts","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"to stop the virus .","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"Obama added","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"that","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"`` faced with this outbreak ,","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"the world is looking to '' the United States to lead international efforts","depth":14},{"id":105,"text":"to combat the virus .","depth":14},{"id":106,"text":"He said","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"the United States is ready to take on that leadership role .","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"`` Here 's the hard truth .","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"In West Africa , Ebola is now an epidemic of the likes","depth":13},{"id":110,"text":"that we have not seen before .","depth":13},{"id":111,"text":"It 's spiraling out of control , ''","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"Obama said .","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"`` If the outbreak is not stopped now ,","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"we could be looking at hundreds of thousands of people","depth":13},{"id":115,"text":"infected","depth":13},{"id":116,"text":"with profound political and economic and security implications for all of us . ''","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"Washington has already committed more than $ 100 million","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"to combat Ebola ,","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"according to the U.S. Agency for International Development .","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"Last week , USAID said","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"it would spend $ 75 million","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"to build treatment facilities","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"and supply them with medical equipment .","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"The Pentagon says","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"it 's working to shift $ 500 million of not yet obligated funds toward the Ebola effort .","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"Public health campaigns will be broadcast through existing networks in Liberia , Sierra Leone and Guinea .","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"The President 's visit to the CDC comes amid escalating criticism from health experts of the global response to the outbreak in West Africa .","depth":6},{"id":128,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":7},{"id":129,"text":"Doctor 'improving ' after Ebola diagnosis","depth":8},{"id":130,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":8},{"id":131,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":8},{"id":132,"text":"Doctor 'improving ' after Ebola diagnosis","depth":8},{"id":133,"text":"02:05","depth":7},{"id":134,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":9},{"id":135,"text":"Why is n't Ebola containment working ?","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":8},{"id":138,"text":"Why is n't Ebola containment working ?","depth":8},{"id":139,"text":"01:44","depth":8},{"id":140,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"Gates Foundation to donate $ 50 million","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":8},{"id":143,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":9},{"id":144,"text":"Gates Foundation to donate $ 50 million","depth":9},{"id":145,"text":"03:23","depth":4},{"id":146,"text":"U.S. officials hope","depth":6},{"id":147,"text":"a more coordinated response on the ground ,","depth":8},{"id":148,"text":"put in place by the United States ,","depth":8},{"id":149,"text":"will encourage other nations to step up their efforts .","depth":7},{"id":150,"text":"`` This is a global threat","depth":8},{"id":151,"text":"and demands a global response , ''","depth":8},{"id":152,"text":"Obama said .","depth":7},{"id":153,"text":"He added","depth":7},{"id":154,"text":"that the international community needs to move faster .","depth":7},{"id":155,"text":"Next week , the U.S. will chair an emergency meeting of the U.N. Security Council","depth":6},{"id":156,"text":"to maximize the response to the Ebola crisis .","depth":6},{"id":157,"text":"The White House will also bring more countries together","depth":6},{"id":158,"text":"to talk about future health threats .","depth":6},{"id":159,"text":"Tuesday , WHO announced","depth":5},{"id":160,"text":"that China dispatched a mobile laboratory team to Sierra Leone","depth":7},{"id":161,"text":"to help test for the virus .","depth":7},{"id":162,"text":"The team of 59 from the Chinese Center for Disease Control includes epidemiologists , clinicians and nurses .","depth":7},{"id":163,"text":"This team will join 115 Chinese medical staff already on the ground in Sierra Leone .","depth":7},{"id":164,"text":"Nongovernmental organizations","depth":10},{"id":165,"text":"that have been fighting this outbreak since its start","depth":10},{"id":166,"text":"reacted positively to Obama 's announcement .","depth":9},{"id":167,"text":"`` The multifaceted response to the Ebola crisis","depth":12},{"id":168,"text":"announced today by President Obama","depth":12},{"id":169,"text":"is what we have been hoping for","depth":12},{"id":170,"text":"and what is needed in Liberia and West Africa , ''","depth":12},{"id":171,"text":"said Bruce Johnson , president of SIM USA .","depth":10},{"id":172,"text":"Two of the three American workers","depth":13},{"id":173,"text":"who contracted Ebola in Liberia","depth":13},{"id":174,"text":"and were evacuated to the United States for treatment","depth":12},{"id":175,"text":"work for SIM .","depth":11},{"id":176,"text":"SIM and other organizations such as Doctors Without Borders","depth":13},{"id":177,"text":"that have been working on the Ebola outbreak since the beginning","depth":13},{"id":178,"text":"have been asking for additional international help for months .","depth":12},{"id":179,"text":"`` Three things are vital right now :","depth":14},{"id":180,"text":"More beds and equipment , more trained medical professionals , and more training of Liberians and West Africans , ''","depth":14},{"id":181,"text":"Johnson said .","depth":13},{"id":182,"text":"`` This current plan addresses these desperate needs . ''","depth":12},{"id":183,"text":"One of the doctors","depth":9},{"id":184,"text":"who had been working with SIM 's clinic in Liberia","depth":10},{"id":185,"text":"when he became infected with the virus","depth":10},{"id":186,"text":"testified Tuesday in front of a joint hearing in Congress","depth":9},{"id":187,"text":"to look at ways","depth":10},{"id":188,"text":"to stop Ebola .","depth":10},{"id":189,"text":"Dr. Kent Brantly urged Congress to provide the extra funds","depth":9},{"id":190,"text":"to fight the outbreak .","depth":9},{"id":191,"text":"Earlier in the day he met with President Obama ,","depth":13},{"id":192,"text":"who told him about the expanded U.S. efforts .","depth":13},{"id":193,"text":"Brantly said","depth":14},{"id":194,"text":"he thanked the President ,","depth":14},{"id":195,"text":"and urged Congress to back this plan up with `` immediate action . ''","depth":13},{"id":196,"text":"`` As a survivor , it is not only my privilege ,","depth":14},{"id":197,"text":"but it is my duty","depth":14},{"id":198,"text":"to speak out on behalf of the people of West Africa","depth":14},{"id":199,"text":"who continue to face unspeakable devastation","depth":15},{"id":200,"text":"because of this horrific disease , ''","depth":15},{"id":201,"text":"Brantly said .","depth":12},{"id":202,"text":"He told the story about a patient","depth":13},{"id":203,"text":"named Francis","depth":14},{"id":204,"text":"who","depth":16},{"id":205,"text":"he believes","depth":16},{"id":206,"text":"may have been saved","depth":15},{"id":207,"text":"had the world acted sooner .","depth":12},{"id":208,"text":"The patient became infected","depth":13},{"id":209,"text":"after carrying a neighbor sick with Ebola to a taxi","depth":14},{"id":210,"text":"to get him to a hospital .","depth":14},{"id":211,"text":"`` If someone had gone alongside Francis","depth":16},{"id":212,"text":"and given him a little education","depth":17},{"id":213,"text":"and given him the equipment","depth":18},{"id":214,"text":"he needed ,","depth":18},{"id":215,"text":"his family would have a father , ''","depth":15},{"id":216,"text":"Brantly said .","depth":14},{"id":217,"text":"Instead his patient died","depth":14},{"id":218,"text":"and the world lost `` this good Samaritan . ''","depth":14},{"id":219,"text":"Brantly went on to respond to the analogy","depth":12},{"id":220,"text":"some have used","depth":12},{"id":221,"text":"to describe Ebola as a fire","depth":12},{"id":222,"text":"burning out of control .","depth":12},{"id":223,"text":"He warned ,","depth":13},{"id":224,"text":"it is a `` fire .","depth":14},{"id":225,"text":"It is a fire straight from the pit of hell . ''","depth":14},{"id":226,"text":"`` We can not fool ourselves into thinking","depth":14},{"id":227,"text":"that the vast Atlantic Ocean will protect us from the flames of this fire , ''","depth":14},{"id":228,"text":"Brantly said .","depth":13},{"id":229,"text":"Move quickly ,","depth":13},{"id":230,"text":"he urged ,","depth":13},{"id":231,"text":"as it is `` the only way","depth":13},{"id":232,"text":"to keep entire nations from being reduced to ashes . ''","depth":13},{"id":233,"text":"There is also a concern about the possibility","depth":10},{"id":234,"text":"that the virus could mutate into an even more dangerous form .","depth":10},{"id":235,"text":"Ebola currently transmits only though contact with bodily fluids ;","depth":10},{"id":236,"text":"a mutation","depth":13},{"id":237,"text":"that allows the virus to spread through the air","depth":13},{"id":238,"text":"would pose a catastrophic threat to people worldwide ,","depth":12},{"id":239,"text":"health experts say .","depth":11},{"id":240,"text":"White House press secretary Josh Earnest said Monday","depth":10},{"id":241,"text":"that there was still a `` very low '' likelihood","depth":11},{"id":242,"text":"the Ebola virus could mutate in a way","depth":12},{"id":243,"text":"that threatens the United States .","depth":12},{"id":244,"text":"`` Right now , the risk of an Ebola outbreak in the United States is very low , ''","depth":11},{"id":245,"text":"he said ,","depth":11},{"id":246,"text":"`` but that risk would only increase","depth":11},{"id":247,"text":"if there were not a robust response on the part of the United States . ''","depth":11},{"id":248,"text":"The President noted a number of precautionary steps","depth":9},{"id":249,"text":"that are being taken in the United States","depth":9},{"id":250,"text":"to prevent the disease from spreading here .","depth":8},{"id":251,"text":"The government has stepped up screening at West African airports .","depth":8},{"id":252,"text":"It has increased education for flight crews","depth":10},{"id":253,"text":"to teach them what to watch for with people","depth":11},{"id":254,"text":"who may be sick .","depth":11},{"id":255,"text":"It has worked with hospitals and health care workers","depth":10},{"id":256,"text":"to prepare them","depth":11},{"id":257,"text":"in case there is a domestic Ebola problem .","depth":11},{"id":258,"text":"Ebola is more than a health threat to West Africa ;","depth":9},{"id":259,"text":"it could become a `` major humanitarian crisis , ''","depth":10},{"id":260,"text":"according to United Nations Under-Secretary-General Valerie Amos ,","depth":10},{"id":261,"text":"if it is not stopped soon enough .","depth":8},{"id":262,"text":"The United Nations said","depth":9},{"id":263,"text":"that many millions more will be needed","depth":10},{"id":264,"text":"to fight the outbreak .","depth":10},{"id":265,"text":"U.N. leaders estimate","depth":11},{"id":266,"text":"they need $ 1 billion","depth":13},{"id":267,"text":"to fight the epidemic ,","depth":13},{"id":268,"text":"with about half needed for the worst-hit country , Liberia .","depth":12},{"id":269,"text":"Political systems and infrastructure are fragile in the countries","depth":12},{"id":270,"text":"where the virus is concentrated .","depth":12},{"id":271,"text":"Liberia Sierra Leone and Guinea are still rebuilding their economies","depth":13},{"id":272,"text":"after suffering through years of civil wars .","depth":13},{"id":273,"text":"`` Now their capacity","depth":16},{"id":274,"text":"to deliver the necessities of daily life for their people","depth":16},{"id":275,"text":"is on the brink of collapse , ''","depth":15},{"id":276,"text":"Amos said .","depth":14},{"id":277,"text":"`` The Ebola outbreak poses a serious threat to their post-conflict recovery . ''","depth":13},{"id":278,"text":"More people are believed to have died in these countries from secondary diseases like malaria and tuberculosis and from chronic illnesses and pregnancies with complications than from Ebola","depth":12},{"id":279,"text":"because the health care systems are so strained .","depth":12},{"id":280,"text":"Heavy rain adds to the risk of waterborne diseases like malaria .","depth":11},{"id":281,"text":"Food security has also become a problem .","depth":12},{"id":282,"text":"Quarantines keep workers from their jobs","depth":14},{"id":283,"text":"and have slowed the delivery of food to certain areas ,","depth":14},{"id":284,"text":"according to the U.N .","depth":13},{"id":285,"text":"`` We must act now","depth":13},{"id":286,"text":"if we want to avoid greater humanitarian consequences in future , ''","depth":13},{"id":287,"text":"Amos said .","depth":12}],"relations":[{"parent":575,"left":0,"right":574,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":574,"left":432,"right":573,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":432,"left":414,"right":431,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":414,"left":306,"right":413,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":306,"left":291,"right":305,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":291,"left":290,"right":4,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":290,"left":289,"right":3,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":289,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":305,"left":296,"right":304,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":296,"left":292,"right":295,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":292,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":295,"left":7,"right":294,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":294,"left":8,"right":293,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":293,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":304,"left":300,"right":303,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":300,"left":299,"right":15,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":299,"left":11,"right":298,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":298,"left":12,"right":297,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":297,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":303,"left":301,"right":302,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":301,"left":16,"right":17,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":302,"left":18,"right":19,"relation":"attr